Text.string: Ugh, a user agreement? Boring! Don't worry, corporations have our best interests at heart. Except Dahl. And Hyperion. Ehhhh... nevermind.
The propaganda center is this way!

Thanks! I'll pre-order your tombstone just in case. Now, those jerks who tried to murder you are the Children of the Vault, a bandit cult who follow their creepy leaders with blind devotion. Which reminds me—if you're going to obey my every beck and call, you'll need an ECHO device!
Heal your wounds, recruit!
Use this health! I need you alive to save me!
This could save your life! Then you owe me a life debt!
Take these supplies!
I'm giving you everything I got!
Use this to shoot people and not die!
Save me!
What's taking so long?!
Get me down!
I'm gonna sharpen my blade on your spine!
Try it out! I rinsed it off myself!
Oof!
Hnnngh... ah!
Ugh, a user agreement? Boring! I'll auto-accept that for you. No one reads those anyway!
This is Shiv, holy influencer of the Children of the Vault! What do you want, Crapbot?
Hello, bloodthirsty maniac. It is I, Claptrap, slayer of the Destroyer and Super-General of the Crimson Raiders. We have you completely surrounded. Open the gates now, and perhaps I will be merciful!
The ECHO-3. Slightly more powerful than the ECHO-2, and twice as expensive. Besides, the ECHO-2 had a tiny issue with spontaneous combustion, so they rebranded those as grenades.
Crapbot, you're gonna be my new chamberpot! I'm gonna poop in your head! Gahaha!
Crapbot, I'm gonna turn you into an electric shaver! For my butt!
NOOO! RECRUUUUUIT!
Recruit! There's no way your supple and delicate body can survive a showdown with Shiv unprotected! Look around for a shield!
You got a shield! Now you're invincible! Not really, but it just might keep Shiv from killing you in one hit! Now let's get you in there, recruit!
You ARE alive! Get me down!
You did it! I'm sa—aghh!
Wow. I did it! I single-handedly took on the COV and sent them packing! Now all that's left is to signal Lilith that the mission is complete!
The magnet controls are on the second floor.
Recruit, hurry up! Get to the magnet controls and save me!
Hellooo? Recruit? Did you abandon the Crimson Raiders? If not, find the magnet controls!
Recruit! Get off your inferior posterior. The controls to the magnet are on the second floor!
Cool.
Ooh, high-tech.
Useful.
Love a good gadget.
Well, the cult's destroyed every other Crimson Raider stronghold, so this'll have to do for now.

Good to see someone survived the attack. I'm Lilith, Commander of the Crimson Raiders. Those bandits you fought are part of a cult hunting for the Vault Map, but you and I are gonna find it first. For now, my scout is waiting for you up ahead. Good luck.
Once we defeat the cult, I'll be famous! And when I'm signing autographs, I need you looking sharp while defending me from my legions of fans-slash-stalkers!
You better find some protection before you take on Shiv!
Look around for a shield, recruit! Try that red chest!
Did you find a shield yet?
I'm sure there's a shield around here somewhere. Like in the red chest that I already told you about.
Score one for the Crimson Raiders. You and Claptrap secure the area. I'm on my way.
Before we wreak our righteous vengeance, you'll need to register your ECHO at this Quick-Change!
S'up.
New Vault Hunter, eh? Name's Marcus. You picked a helluva time to join the Crimson Raiders, heh-heh.
Voice in my head. Weird.
That voice. Was that another Siren?
She spoke inside my mind. Strange.
Lady in my head. Got it.
Good! I'm locked, loaded, and ready to loot.
Finally. I'm itching for a fight.
Excellent. The hunt begins.
About time. Let's have some fun.
Moze, Gunner First Class, ex-Vladof Mechanized Infantry.
Surely you know who I am. The Tiger of Partali? Crime-fighter? Warrior for peace?||Gch. It's Amara.
You are allowed to call me FL4K, until I decide if I am going to kill you.
Zane. Zane Flynt.
Take it!
Take the ECHO, recruit!
Don't you like free stuff? Take it!
We can't get to the shooting and looting part until you take the ECHO!

Now listen up, recruit. Lilith ordered us to take over a Children of the Vault propaganda center. Time to show those culty weirdos that no one messes with the Crimson Raiders! Follow me, recruit! TO GLORY!
Use the Quick-Change, recruit!
You look terrible! Use the Quick-Change already!
More like Super-Slow-and-Boring Change! Because you're slow! And boring! And you haven't even changed your outfit yet!
Recruit. I'm on my non-existent knees here. Please... use the Quick-Change!
In the name of the Almighty Robot Policeman, USE THE QUICK-CHANGE!
You look awful!||—ly attractive! Saved it.
Recruit, get that gate open! That's an order from your superior officer!
You did it! Best recruit EVER! But don't get cocky.
I'm not designed for that!
I know Claptrap can be a little... Claptrap, but he's still one of us. You're gonna have to save him. I'll be there soon.
There might be a shield in that special red chest over there!
Hey, Shiiiiv! All your dumb friends are dead! I challenge you to a trial by combat! But because I'm stuck to this magnet, my loyal champion shall vanquish you in my stead.
That's a KIA on the knife-wielding maniac. Super dead.
Knocked out in the first round. Hnh. I thought Pandora was going to give me a challenge!
It seems the humans on Pandora are even more savage than the beasts.
Seemed like a nice enough fella, all things told. My kinda maniac.
Hey, killer. Let's chat.
Moze. And you're the voice in my head, right?
I am Amara. Nice tattoos, Siren sister. You must be the voice in my head.
I'm FL4K. And your voice was in my head. Explain yourself.
I'm Zane. And you're the lady from my brain!
This way, recruit!
Today's weaponry includes a new gun mode. Try it out!
Helllooooo? Anyone there?
Lilith! I can safely report that Operation Trojan Claptrap was a complete success! I did it all by myself!
I'll bet.
The propaganda center is up ahead. Those cultists have been killing Crimson Raiders left and right. They totally suck skag balls! But I've got a fool-proof plan to kick their culty asses!
This is your stop, Vault Hunter.
Wait here. I'll talk my way in, become their king, and then you'll surprise-slaughter them in cold blood. Watch and learn, recruit!
They might call themselves Children of the Vault, but they're still bandits, and bandits are incredibly stupid!
Try to stay alive. I'd hate to lose a new customer, heh-heh.
Recruit! They've seen through my air-tight ruse! Save me!
Help!
And welcome to Pandora!
These guns, like myself, aren't beholden to their primary function! I can dance! And SING! [singing] And some guns now include an alternate shooting mode! Try it out!

Yeah, about that... not the weirdest thing you're gonna see on Pandora. But seriously—thanks for answering my call. We might not have the numbers, but with a badass like you, we've got a fighting chance. Welcome to the Crimson Raiders.
Hey! You must be the new recruit! I am a CL4P-TP steward bot, but you can just call me... General Claptrap of the Crimson Raiders! What's your name?
Follow me, recruit!
Have you never seen someone jump before?
Leap across that chasm!
Jump, recruit!
Do they not teach jumping in school anymore? Kids these days!
Now take your gun, recruit! You're gonna need it.
Kill the heretics! In the name of the Calypsos!
Okay, we're going to surrender! Please don't kill us, Crapbot.
We did it... I did it! Another victory for the Crimson Raiders. Hey, I feel funny. What's... happening to me?
Gahahahahaha! Agahagaha!
Hey, HEY! Let go of me!
Come on in, heretic! I haven't met my sacrifice quota for the day!
That's what I thought! Open the doors immediately for your new king!
Recruit? Are you dead? If not, get me down! The controls are on the second floor!
I'm over heeeeere!
Let my melodious voice be your guide!
Did you fall asleep standing up?
Follow me with blind devotion!
A locked gate?! No! This can't be happening. The entire mission is ruined! Think, Claptrap, think! You're brave! And powerful! And people always do what you tell them to!||That's it!
Didja find a way to open the gate yet? The fate of Pandora depends on it maybe!
Check that junk heap over there! That gate is really mucking up our mission! Mucking, I say!
Aww, man. We're never getting past this gate! I'll never be famous! Plus, justice and stuff.
How's it going? If I were you, and I'm super glad I'm not, I'd check that car over there.
Easy, easy. I'm, uh... I'm coming out. Just wait. Right. There!
Go on, use your beautiful and powerful arms to mantle over the ledge.
One jump just won't cut it! You need some kind of... double... jump to get up here.
You came an awful long way to get stuck in a ditch! Pull yourself out, recruit!
To grab the ledge, jump, then jump again! I didn't say it made sense.
I hid a weapons cache nearby. Stay quiet and follow my every move. It's STEALTH time!

Stealthy-time! Gonna walk over here, and—gonna turn! And I'm gonna go over here, super-duper quiet!||Tip-toein' over here, gonna spin around, I'm so—oof!||So quiet! So super-duper-duper-duper QUIET!||Oh, that was a bit too loud!||Stealth-slide!
Perfect! Once we complete our mission, Lilith HAS to promote me to Super-General!
Stand back!
You did say “stealth”, right?
So we're throwing stealth out the window?
That was stealth? How have you survived this long?
Great, I'm sure there's some people on the moon who didn't hear that.
So, what's your name, killer?
Relax. On Pandora, it's actually super weird if something's NOT exploding!
Uh... yeah. Let me think about that.
Gah!
Whoa—aagh!
Ow! My exhaust port.
Take this ammo, recruit!
Use this ammo to kill the bad guys!
Put these bullets into the bad guys! That's a direct order!
